Network

Class LoginAttempt

  • java.lang.Object
    • Network.LoginAttempt
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class LoginAttempt
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A LoginAttempt is what a Client sends when attempting to login to the server. If the LoginAttempt is successful, they will be granted access to the game. If not, then the game will alert them what is wrong. Possible problems include an incorrect password or a banned username.
    Author:
    Michael Hogue
